    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-chem.200700118.pdf_7_5",
    "text": "Where comparisons can be made, there is good agreement between the theoretical and experimental wavenumbers. Both the direction and magnitude of the wavenumber shifts found experimentally to be induced by complexation are reproduced by the calculations. For example, the experimental (HF) shift of -435.3 cm ' is matched theoretically by a shift of -437.9 cm'. Small blue shifts of the fundamentals that could be observed for the H,C-S subunit are also anticipated satisfactorily by the calculations. Low intensity in terms of IR absorption, masking by more intense absorptions of other species, and wavenumbers falling below the minimum threshold of the present measurements are then explanations sufficient to account for the fundamentals of H,C SHF and D,C-SDF that escaped detection. Despite these omissions, though, we have little doubt that D has thus been identified correctly.",
